Pro-American Submission of S. Korean Authorities Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued information bulletin No. 885 on Saturday, denouncing the despicable pro-American submission of the south Korean authorities over the issue of the withdrawal of the U.S. troops' oil pipe.
 The controversial oil pipe was laid in 1972 by the U.S. imperialist aggression troops in south Korea for oil transport. It was for the exclusive use of the U.S. troops extending a total of 452 km from Phohang in North Kyongsang Province to Uijongbu of Kyonggi Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. troops in south Korea had used this oil pipe and handed it over to the south Korean authorities in 1992 when its days have expired. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean public says that the astronomic amount of expenses needed for the dissolution of the old oil pipe and rehabilitation of environment can not be borne by the "tax collected from the people" and asserts that the U.S. military side should bear all the expenses as it had built and used it, the information bulletin noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the U.S. troops stationed in south Korea are forcing south Korea to bear all the expenses and the south Korean authorities, yielding to it, are taking a pro-American submissive attitude that the government should bear the expenses for the withdrawal of the oil pipe as it had already taken it over and registered it as state property. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an unpardonable criminal act of doing harm to the dignity, interests and sovereignty of the nation because it shows the aggressive and dominationist stand of the U.S. toward south Korea and the slavish position of the south Korean authorities as henchmen of a colony who cannot live a moment unless they curry favor with the U.S.

S. Korean Policy of Opening Rice Market Protested 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- South Korean peasants reportedly held demonstrations of ploughing paddy fields before harvest in 22 cities and counties across south Korea including North Jolla Province, south Korean Kangwon Province, North and South Kyongsang provinces, and North and South Chungchong provinces on September 22 in protest against the authorities' policy of opening rice market.
 That day peasants under the south Korean Federation of Peasants Associations held a press conference in a paddy field in Solsong-myon, Richon City, Kyonggi Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference speakers called upon all the people to join in the struggle to protect the rice, their sovereign right and life, and block the opening of rice market, saying they will wage a persistent struggle including the one million-peasants signature campaign for the abandonment of rice harvest in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release and a memorandum on abandoning rice harvest were read out at the press conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the conference the peasants ploughed paddy fields with a tractor.

Kim Jong Il's Works Published in Over 100 Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- Famous works of leader Kim Jong Il have been published and disseminated worldwide amid the deep concern of the progressive humankind from the early 1980s.
 According to the data available, nearly 810,000 copies of at least 60 kinds of his works have been brought out in collection and booklet by many publishing houses, political parties and organizations of over 100 countries, including the Paleya Publishing House of Russia, the Book Association Publishing House of Cuba, the Lao State Publishing House, the National Education Publishing House of Guinea, the Communist Party of Venezuela and the Group of Dialectical Materialists of Italy, for more than 20 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Enugu Publishing House of Nigeria and the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association published works "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction" and "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" in booklet. Their prefaces said the works clarifying the fundamental principle to be maintained in carrying out the popular masses' cause of independence, the cause of socialism, serve as a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon to cope with the hegemonic "globalization" of the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony of releasing "On the Juche Idea", a collection of works, which carries works "On the Juche Idea", "On Some Questions in Understanding the Juche Philosophy", "Let Us Advance under the Banner of Marxism-Leninism and the Juche Idea", "On Some Problems of Education in the Juche Idea" and "On Establishing the Juche Outlook on the Revolution" the secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Kyrgyzstan said that they will study hard the works to have deeper understanding of the Juche idea and actively propagandize it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Collections of works and booklets published in national languages of over 40 countries have been disseminated in all parts of the five continents, evoking great repercussions from the political and public circles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The New Communist Party of Britain, the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, the Bangladesh People's League, the Workers' Party of Mexico and other progressive political parties of different countries convened secretariat meetings and emergency meetings to define the works as must books and action programmes. They took various steps to publish, carry and study the works so as to be disseminated among people of all social strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, national committees and groups for the study of Kim Jong Il's works were formed in India, Democratic Congo, Denmark, Austria, Peru and many other countries and seminars and lectures on works held on hundreds of occasions every year under the sponsorship of political parties and organizations.

Unity and Cooperation Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The international conference of Asian political parties held in Beijing some time ago discussed the issues of regional security and multi-party cooperation, economic growth, social progress, etc., on the theme "exchange, cooperation and development" and adopted the "2004 Beijing Declaration."
 The spirit and success of the conference show the growing aspiration and enthusiasm of regional people to step up the building of independent and prospering new Asia by strengthening unity and cooperation, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Asian people are now faced with the task to realize the cause of global independence, the cause of Asian independence, the article says, and goes on:
 To strengthen unity and cooperation is an important guarantee for the building of independent and prospering new Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the Asian countries strengthen unity and cooperation they are able to settle various issues including insufficient funds and resources and scientific and technological issues. In order to build new Asia it is important for all the Asian countries to achieve sincere unity and disinterested cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the countries can be united under the banner of friendship and cooperation irrespective of difference in ideology, system and religious belief. What is important here is to keep the principle of independence, equality and mutual respect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity and cooperation are urgently required under the condition in which the imperialists are intensifying the moves for aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is now working hard to realize its wild ambition by way of strength while intensifying the policy of confrontation in Asia. To this end, it is building its new military bases in Asian countries and concentrating huge aggression armed forces there. Asian countries and people should get all the aggression military bases and armed forces withdrawn, which threaten peace and security in Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is the consistent policy of the DPRK government to achieve unity and cooperation with Asian countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will firmly unite and closely cooperate with Asian people in carrying out the common cause of building independent, peaceful and prospering new Asia.

Struggle for Withdrawal of U.S. Troops from S. Korea Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- The people from all walks of life in south Korea should wage more dynamic struggle to get the U.S. troops withdrawn from south Korea to put an end to its military occupation for the sake of their destiny in conformity with the expectation and aspiration of the whole nation, stresses Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article.
 The struggle to terminate the U.S. military occupation of south Korea and its policy of domination is a just patriotic struggle for the dignity and interests of the Korean nation, and its independent development cannot be expected without the struggle, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This struggle is a patriotic struggle to put an end to the history of the national division and achieve national reunification and a struggle to defend the peace of the country and the security of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation had waged a bloody struggle for national reunification, aspiring after it even in dream, and eventually opened the era of the June 15 joint declaration as it could not sustain any longer the painful misfortune and sufferings, disgrace and tragedy imposed by the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Nevertheless, the U.S. occupationist forces are remaining in south Korea under the signboard of the "U.N. forces", putting the brake in national reconciliation and cooperation and laying stumbling blocks in the way of national reunification. It is a prerequisite for reunification and a patriotic struggle for the supreme interests of the nation to drive out of this land the U.S. imperialist aggression troops which are interfering and obstructing the patriotic reunification movement of the Korean nation against their loud-mouthed advertisement of "peace" and "reunification" of the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation on the Korean peninsula is reaching a very dangerous pitch at which a war may break out any moment. It is clear that if a war breaks out on this land owing to the reckless military provocation of the U.S. imperialist bellicose elements, it will immediately turn into a nuclear war and impose unpredictable disasters upon the Koreans in the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that the peace of the country and the security of the nation cannot be defended as long as the U.S. imperialist aggression troops remain in this land, now that the U.S. criminal attempt to unleash a second war for aggression in the Korean peninsula at any cost has become clear and the movement of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops stationed in south Korea, its field executor, is reaching a reckless stage.

Japan's Moves for Overseas Aggression Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 26 (KCNA) -- Japan is letting out a stream of words that it should relax the "restraint of arms buildup and three principles of arms export" and re-prescribe the overseas activity of its "Self-Defense Forces" as its main duty, not offbeat one at present.
 In this regard, the advisory body of the Japanese prime minister totally revised the present "plan for fundamental defense capability" based on the "exclusive defense" policy and decided to present to the prime minister an inclusive "report on defense", which deals with such issues of introducing long-range large transport planes necessary for overseas dispatch of the SDF and providing legal conditions for possible production of the missile defense system under Japan-U.S. joint research. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This fully proves that Japan is trying to change the concept of "defense", which it has superficially maintained in the course of realizing its ambition to become a military giant, into an offensive one and openly convert the SDF into armed forces for overseas invasion. Minju Joson Sunday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that Japan is now readjusting the main structure of the Ground SDF allegedly to cope with attacks and surprise strikes and thus prevent "terrorism" and "infiltration of commandoes", the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's desperate military moves under the pretext of coping with "terrorism" are none other than a serious challenge to the aspiration of the international community after the peace and stability of Northeast Asia as they are a manifestation of its ambition for militaristic overseas invasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the basic objective of Japan to paint itself as a war state at an early date by realizing its long-cherished ambition for militaristic overseas expansion and conversion into a military power, availing itself of the global trend of "anti-terrorism". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not difficult to guess what holocaust Asia and the rest of the world would suffer if Japan, which is fervent with revenging itself on its defeat in the Second World War, provokes a war of overseas invasion after having complete offensive capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noon day that the Korean peninsula would be the first target of Japan's attack for overseas invasion. Accordingly, the DPRK is watching the recent military moves of Japan with high vigilance and cannot but get fully ready to cope with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should immediately stop its political rashness hastening its self-destruction.

Appeal on Situation Published in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly held an emergency meeting on September 20 at which an appeal on the situation to the youth and students was published.
 It is the task of all the three million students to put an end to the division of the nation caused by outsiders and the anti-reunification moves of the conservative forces, the appeal noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though we live in different places and environment, we of the same blood, have seen sovereignty wantonly violated by outsiders, subject to their ceaseless aggression and plunder. The students have been well aware of the fact that it is the United States that threatens the security of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the "Security Law" is an anti-reunification law aimed to hamstring all efforts for the reunification of the country, it called for getting the SL abolished and usher in a new era, the era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also called upon the students to turn out as one in the struggle to achieve the national independence and national reunification and implement the June 15 joint declaration.

Solidarity Society for Withdrawal of U.S. Troops Formed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The Anti-U.S., Anti-War Solidarity Society for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Troops from South Korea was reportedly formed with due ceremony at Sogang University in Seoul on Sept. 21.
 Speakers at the ceremony stressed that they have formed the society to make 2005 a year for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops, a year of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A working orientation of the society was published at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization said it would wage the struggle to shatter the moves for a nuclear war against the north, oppose troops dispatch and arms buildup and abolish the U.S. military bases in close combination with the massive struggle to get the U.S. troops withdrawn from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It confirmed it as its major work to publish books carrying the contents including the relocation of the U.S. troops, the issue of the Korean peninsula, the history of the U.S. troops' crimes and their withdrawal and conduct the work for policy study and information activities for the people such as seminar on the issue of the U.S. troops and opening of homepage for their withdrawal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It published its working plan carrying the contents such as the operation of the day of the action to get the U.S. troops withdrawn from south Korea once in a week and intensive struggle, information activities in street, the struggle for traveling the U.S. military bases across south Korea and candlelight cultural festival once in a month.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Saturday dedicates an article to the 17th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's celebrated work on vigorously advancing along the road of socialism under the uplifted banner of anti-imperialist struggle.
 The article says: The work was published on September 25, Juche 76 (1987). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It calls for vigorously advancing along the road of socialism under the uplifted banner of anti-imperialist struggle as required by the prevailing complicated situation of the revolution. It clarifies on a scientific basis the serious political and economic crisis of bluffing modern imperialism, the issue of its inevitable ruin and issues arising in increasing the driving force of revolution. The period since the publication of the work was one of the proud struggle in which the cause of socialism advanced victoriously under the banner of anti-imperialist struggle and the validity of Kim Jong Il's ideas and theories and the greatness of his leadership have been clearly proved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set out the theory and strategy and tactics of awakening and organizing masses and training core elements among them to suit the changed situation and conditions in recent years, thus strengthening and developing the revolutionary forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He made a deep analysis of the socio-class relations and on this basis set out the idea and theory of organizing the revolutionary forces with the People's Army as a core force and a driving force on the principle of placing the army before the working class. This serves as immortal guidelines in drastically augmenting the driving force of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the banner of Songun held aloft by him serves as the most powerful weapon in the present anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle. Revolution can emerge victorious only when the military capacity of the country is increased in every way and the U.S. imperialists' aggression and war moves are decisively foiled in the indomitable spirit that one must fight against the imperialists and class enemies to a finish. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will defend their ideology, system and cause at the cost of their lives and always emerge victors in the confrontation with the U.S. thanks to Kim Jong Il who is leading the cause of independence against imperialism to victory.
